title: Japanese SAR company iQPS to launch with Rocket Lab after Virgin Orbit bankruptcy
summary: A Japanese firm developing a constellation of SAR satellites is the latest to turn to Rocket Lab after the bankruptcy of rival launch company Virgin Orbit.

title: Rocket Lab pushes to get launch business back on track, with 22 Electron missions booked next year
summary: Rocket Lab is pushing to get its launch business back on track by the end of the year, reporting on Wednesday third-quarter results that saw continued strength in its space systems division.

title: Rocket Lab plans to resume Electron launches in late November
summary: Rocket Lab expects to resume Electron launches in late November after concluding a “largely improbable” combination of events caused the vehicle’s previous launch to fail.
